Only 12.3% of US patients practice

5
00:00:19,759 --> 00:00:25,020
primary care versus
around 50% in France.

6
00:00:25,020 --> 00:00:30,540
The same comparison holds true with
other advanced industrialized nations.

7
00:00:30,540 --> 00:00:32,790
You can see here, the U.S.

8
00:00:32,790 --> 00:00:37,550
lags substantially in the percentage
of primary care physicians.

9
00:00:38,630 --> 00:00:40,443
The full reasons are beyond
the scope of this course.

10
00:00:40,443 --> 00:00:44,884
But one of them is that specialist,
shown in green here,

11
